        "question": "Solve $(\\frac{1}{27})^{x} = 9^{2-x}$.",
        "options": [
          "$x = -4$",
          "$x = 4$",
          "$x = 2$",
          "$x = -2$"
        ],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "Rewrite with base 3: $\\frac{1}{27} = 3^{-3}$, $9 = 3^2$. So $(3^{-3})^x = (3^2)^{2-x}$ ‚Üí $3^{-3x} = 3^{4-2x}$. Equate: $-3x = 4 - 2x$ ‚Üí $-x = 4$ ‚Üí $x = -4$."
